content: This service was fine (counselors were very nice) until they told me they don't take my insurance despite accepting it at sign up and then charging me $75 for medication they didn't even send to the right pharmacy. Had to dispute and issue stop payment through my bank. Buyer beware.

I signed up on January 10, 2022, then canceled on January 12, 2022. It just wasn't in my budget. Since then, I have had problems. It was confirmed on January 12, 2022 by a coordinator, Jayvee R., that my account had been canceled. On February 11, 2022, Cerebral charged me $85. I immediately contacted Cerebral via their support email to request a refund and to explain my frustration that this happened. I still haven't received a response or refund. I'm really disappointed and angry.

Go anywhere else. The cheapest plan is $85 just for medication and one visit a month at their time. It is not therapy, strictly a follow-up. Impossible to schedule meetings or connect to the meetings and I haven't gotten medication in 2 months. Complete waste of money
Apparently they can't prescribe medication to someone who's already on medication. Waste of money

Will update my review once I've actually met with the care team. Mediocre review so far because you get charged the monthly fee before you even meet with anybody. Almost 3 weeks into signing up and I've already paid for a service that I can't actually use yet.
If you are seeking a full range of treatment for ADHD and you have not been diagnosed by a Neuropsych, Cerebral will NOT be able to provide this. Skip the step and get a diagnosis first

I would give no stars if that was an option. I ended up needing to cancel this service. Not only was my account canceled a week after I canceled it (I was told it would only take 2 days), they also STILL charged my account AFTER it was canceled! Highly disappointed and will not be back!
Feeling better already!

App works okay, but the company is terrible and they don't know how it works. If you are reading these reviews and unsure if you should stick with Cerebral then take my advice, don't. This company doesn't care about you at all as you are just a monthly payment to them. They seek to exploit the mentally ill for profit and they make false promises and dont follow through. They treat their employees very poorly. I was with them for 3 months and literally lost 4 people that were assigned to me.
Physically setting $85 dollars on fire would have been more beneficial to my mental health than signing up for this joke service.

Way too expensive and doesn't accept enough insurance. People ask why mental health in America sucks, well if it's hidden behind a pay wall and heavily outpaces regular health costs it's pretty obvious why. It's a specialist field that charge enough they're part of the problem. Need regulation to force the prices down since they can't be trusted to do it themselves without offering you a subpar service. Average salary is 31k in America, they can't afford this service at its best.
Therapist was more concerned with rules and regulations, rather than treating me, the patient, itself. NO refills given, either on medications. Not nice.

They said 26/week for your first month then when I paid I was charged 30. Then the next screen said "do you want to add therapy and medication planning for an extra 56?" Um I thought that's what I was already paying for? I clicked it and it immediately tried charging me an extra 109.
Nice app, great service

I've been using Cerebral for roughly 4 months and it's been a life saving service for me.I was very cautious with my expectations signing up,but was in such a bad place I was willing to try. It is costly without insurance,but it would be more costly for me to go to my primary,or a psychiatrist regularly.My prescriber has been a rock for me, she has made herself very available to me more than any doctor has for any help I need. I hope they continue to earn my trust.
it's an easy way to get access to help as you needed. I only wish there were more informational articles and more therapeutic activities
incredibly helpful mental health service. The app makes it that much more accessible and eaay to use.

this is lifesaving, truly helping me to cope with the extreme anxiety and past trauma that I have kept buried inside for so long. It is affecting everything in my life from my relationship with my to my parents and my husband. I have to break this chain. And Cerebral has been great giving me the tools I need to cope and beat this. Thanks Cerebral!
They do not help anyone with substance abuse history or suicidal thoughts no matter how rare

Per their website my insurance should have been accepted, but after entering the info/taking pics of my card I'm told otherwise & all costs had to be paid out of pocket. You have to enter your debit card # before you can enter your insurance info, so they already had my card on file & had billed it before I'd even completed signing up. Also, they can not prescribe medications that I'm currently taking because of where I live, so they wouldn't have been able to fully help me anyway.
I've been having the same issues just like many of the other people who have made reviews. No actually help has been provided and I've been with them for 2 months now.

Complete waste of money. It takes an entire month to get an appointment and you can't do anything or get any help until your first appointment - therefore you pay for nothing the first month. A more effective as less expensive plan is to continue to talk to a wall and buy the drugs you need off the street.
it has helped so much already!

Cerebral is great until you try to cancel. I asked for my account to be canceled since I had not been using the service in months and the representative tried to sell me on additional discounts. This prolonged the process especially since they don't typically respond that day. I was then charged for another month even after they finally processed my cancelation request. I then tried to call someone to resolve this issue but was left on hold for almost an hour.
Pill pushers
replyContent: Hi Desiree, thanks for writing in. We are so glad to hear that you're finding your time at Cerebral to be helpful. content: Cerebral advertising a customized, deliberate care plan only to prescribe the most 'better cover our asses' medications available is not only misleading but a gross overpromise. If it had ever crossed my mind that knocking myself out on moderate strength antihistamine (what Cerebral prescribed me for my severe anxiety) was at all a comprehensive treatment for chronic anxiety, I'd go buy some Benadryl for a fraction of the price I spent on Cerebral. Really, really unhelpful.
This app is a scam. They will take your money than they won't have services for you. Do not give them any money you have been warned.
has been a godsend

Just save yourself time ,money and frustration by skipping over this app . The video calls rarely work and you cannot have calls outside of their "secure" service . What's so wrong with just using webex ?
so easy and accommodating!

I used this for therapy for four months. You have to pre pay, so when your therapist goes on vacation, has no available appointments that week, or like mine, quits, you do not get your money back. They will give you credits for future months, but I do not want all of these credits for missed sessions that were out of my control. I absolutely do not think it is fair that you prepay $250 a month and then don't always get services.

Prescribers, therapists, and coordinators are constantly changing. The prescribers are rarely psychiatrists & don't seem to be knowledgeable. The meds prescribed caused me to go into serotonin syndrome every time they prescribed. I thought I had finally found help for my depression/anxiety/insomnia, but I the trauma of going through all this has made my mental condition even worse. Please don't put yourself through this.
Great

The app is easy to navigate and the Cerebral staff, physicians, counselors and coordinators are amazing, nice, accommodating and easy to talk to. I love having my mental health needs at my fingertips, anywhere and anytime.

Honestly only gave 1 star because I had to give something to leave a review. Absolutely wish I would have read the reviews prior to my "trial". I have filled out the survey to cancel my account three times now and still have not heard back. I have also requested a refund as my appointments were cancelled and rescheduled like so many other reviews. I can say I honestly feel bad for someone desperately seeking help. Don't waste your time and money with this app! Complete SCAM!
A fantastic app, especially if you don't have insurance coverage for mental health. You can still get help.

IMPOSSIBLE to schedule an appointment once you pay. Even worse is trying to get across to their support team. I've messaged my therapist-who they advertise as being available 24/7-because we were supposed to reschedule a weekly session (I pay for one session a week) The week is almost over and no word on getting another session. No one picks up the phone or answers messages, it's been over a day since I got any response from him. I was offered 30% compensation for their mistakes; never again
These guys are awful.
love the fact that is so straight forward.
still new to this but so far, everyone is really receptive and I'm enjoying it
best mental Healthcare I have received in my life. most mentally stable I have been since I was a teen. thank you cerebral.
I'm just beginning but I've been given wonderful strategies and activities to do to keep my mind busy when it's overloaded. my care counselor has been wonderful! Can't wait for my next session.
I haven't been contacted by anyone in a month after they've had to switch me between people multiple times. No consistency or stability.

DRUG PEDDLERS! One 15 minute conversation and all of a sudden unnecessary drugs are being shipped to me and after paying for a standard insurance based subscription my "care coordinator" informs me that if I want talk therapy, which is all I really wanted, then I have to pay hundreds of dollars more per month out of pocket. Stop pushing drugs and try just helping people. I wish I had read other reviews more thoroughly because this seems to be the prevailing experience.
RIP off compared to all other sites
A complete let down after almost a year of wasted money.

met with my therapist 2 days after signing up I really do like her as well having this many options is wonderful no more booking weeks out to start price is actually cheaper than going to my normal therapist
just installed a couple days ago and waiting for appointment. check-ins are a nice thing they do

"cancel anytime" is just an outright lie. Be prepared to spend some time if you should decide to cancel your membership. I might update my review if they actually cancel my membership before charging my debit card again.
not sure what to do

The grounding techniques on this app have really helped me during my panic attacks. I love that my therapist is just a text away and I can reach out when I need to. I'm extremely thankful for this service.

It's clear that the counselors are not in very good communication with the app staff. Once you get in you are bounced around between counselors. You have to see two different ones, a Prescriber and a Care Counselor. This is confusing and again, these are two teams that don't talk to each other and know what's going on. Very expensive. 2 stars because I was able to get diagnosed and prescribed, and this structure may bring mental health care to those who can't access it, but needs to be better.
HUNDREDS OF DOLLARS FOR TREATMENT. Signed up, canceled immediately, and they wont give me a full refund. Awful marketing and very misleading
Very professional, understanding, and a joy to deal with/"open up to" if you need such a thing
App works fine but the counselors don't do their job. It's really a waste of time.
